        "title": "Add MiniMax M3 support to the bundled MiniMax provider",
        "body": "## Summary\n\nThis PR adds bundled MiniMax support for `MiniMax-M3` and makes it the default MiniMax text model.\n\n- add `MiniMax-M3` model ids, catalog metadata, and provider constants\n- keep `MiniMax-M2.7` and `MiniMax-M2.7-highspeed` available in the bundled MiniMax catalog\n- switch MiniMax onboarding, config examples, docs, and PDF text extraction defaults to `MiniMax-M3`\n- preserve `/fast` rewriting for `MiniMax-M2.7 -> MiniMax-M2.7-highspeed`; `MiniMax-M3` has no highspeed variant and stays unchanged\n- add MiniMax M3 tiered pricing metadata and update shared cost calculation so tiered provider pricing is applied at runtime\n\nCloses #88868.\n\n## Verification\n\n- `node scripts/run-vitest.mjs extensions/minimax/model-definitions.test.ts`\n- `node scripts/run-vitest.mjs extensions/minimax/onboard.test.ts`\n- `node scripts/run-vitest.mjs extensions/minimax/index.test.ts`\n- `node scripts/run-vitest.mjs src/llm/providers/stream-wrappers/minimax.test.ts`\n- `node scripts/run-vitest.mjs src/plugin-sdk/provider-stream.test.ts`\n- `node scripts/run-vitest.mjs src/agents/models-config.providers.minimax.test.ts`\n- `node scripts/run-vitest.mjs src/llm/model-utils.test.ts`\n- `node scripts/run-vitest.mjs src/agents/model-compat.test.ts`\n- `node scripts/run-vitest.mjs src/agents/minimax-docs.test.ts`\n- `pnpm build`\n\n## Real behavior proof\n\nBehavior addressed: bundled MiniMax provider now exposes `MiniMax-M3` as the default text model, keeps both M2.7 variants available, and applies the published M3 tiered pricing in cost calculation.\nReal environment tested: local source checkout on branch `codex/minimax-m3-support`.\nExact steps or command run after this patch: the focused Vitest commands above plus `pnpm build`.\nEvidence after fix: MiniMax provider tests, docs tests, and shared model cost tests pass with `MiniMax-M3` defaults and tiered pricing assertions.\nObserved result after fix: onboarding/config/docs point at `MiniMax-M3`, `/fast` still upgrades only M2.7, and runtime cost calculation supports the M3 `<512K` and `512K-1M` pricing tiers.\nWhat was not tested: live MiniMax API calls against a real account.\n",
